President Obama has nominated Kelvin Washington, the current Sheriff of Williamsburg County in South Carolina, to be the U.S. Marshal for the District of South Carolina. Washington has dedicated his career to protecting the people of South Carolina and has shown courage and persistence in the pursuit of justice. He has been with the Williamsburg County Sheriff's Office since 1993 and has risen through the ranks to his current position. In addition, Washington has been an Adjunct Professor at Charleston Southern University and Horry-Georgetown Technical College, teaching in the Criminal Justice Division since 2007. He started his law enforcement career with the City of Florence Police Department and has a Master of Science degree in criminal justice from Troy University and a Bachelor of Science degree in criminal justice from American Intercontinental University.